{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_1lichtenstein_ver02/data/sn83045462/00280601688/1938011101/0051.xml":{"full_text":"Break in Japanese Issues\nand Rails\u2019 Drop Help\nUnsettle Market.\nBond Averages\n20 10 10 10\nRails. Indust Util. P en\nNet change- \u2014.1 Unc. Unc. \u2014.3\nToday, noon 70.1 97.3 91.6 66.6\nPrev. day... 70.2 97.3 91.6 66.9\nMonth ago. 73.8 96.7 91,9 65.6\nYear ago... 98.5 104.0 102.6 73.4\n1937-8 high. 99.0 104.4 102.8 74.7\n1937-8 low.. 69.3 95.5 90.3 64.2\n1936 high_\u00bb8.2 104.4 103.1 73.0\n1936 low_ 86.9 101.8 99.3 67.6\n1932 low.... 45.8 40.0 64.6 42.2\n1928 high...101.1 98.9 102.9 100.5\n10 Low-Yield Bonds.\nNoon -106.9 Prev. day. 106.8\nMonth ago 106.7 Year ago. 113.6\n1937-8 hl'h 113.7 1937-8 low 105.6\n1936 high. 113.5 1936 low.. 110.2\n1928 high. 104.4 1932 low.. 86.8\n(Comolled or the Associated Preu.)\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK. Jan. 11\u2014 A break in\nJapanese bands and renewed declines\nin some speculative rail issues helped\nunsettle the bond market today\nand checked earlier recovery tend\nencies in many corporate obligations.\nLosses in the Japan group in\nlate tradirfg ranged to 4 and 5 points\nIn what apparently was an unfavor\nable reaction to reports formal war\nmight be declared on China in the\nPar Eastern conflict. Among the\nheaviest losers were Japan 612s and\n5\u20182S, Tokio City 5!2s and Taiwan\nElectric Power 5!2s.\nLiquidation in rails centered in\nErie and Baltimore Js Ohio loans,\nresulting in losses running to nearly\n7 points in a few infrequently traded\nIssues, such as Erie First 4s. Several\nErie liens were freely offered, notably\nthe 5s of 1975.\nBetter-grade corporate bonds mostly\nheld to a narrow path in quiet trading\nand some pushed ahead for moderate i\ngains. Lehigh Valley Coal bonds ex- j\npanded previous rally gains.\nWashington Exchange\nSALES\u2014AFTER CALL.\nPotomac Electric Power 6% pfd.\u20142\nat 113U\nCity Suburban 5s\u2014$1,000 at 55,\n$1,000 at 55.\nBid and Asked Prices.\nBO